Cyber Security Certification Roadmap
====================================

Inspiration & Acknowledgements
------------------------------

This project was inspired by, and pays respect to, the following public works:

  * Paul Jerimy's Security Certification Roadmap
    https://pauljerimy.com/security-certification-roadmap/

  * CyberDudeKZ's Security Cert Roadmap
    https://cyberdudekz.github.io/security-cert-roadmap/

We are grateful to both authors for advancing public knowledge in this space.

Independent Compilation
-----------------------

The certification list, domain taxonomy, tier rubric, JSON schema, JavaScript,
HTML, CSS, and evaluation skills in this repository were authored
independently by the contributors of this project. No data, layout, code, or
images were copied from the inspiration sources above.

Where the inspiration sources are referenced from a per-certification
`sources[]` entry, the entry is tagged `"use": "inspiration_only"` to make
the relationship machine-readable: the link is acknowledgement, not data
provenance.

Authoritative Source Agencies
-----------------------------

For Japanese certifications (mode toggle), authoritative information is
sourced from:

  * IPA (Information-technology Promotion Agency, Japan) - https://www.ipa.go.jp/
  * METI (Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry) - https://www.meti.go.jp/
  * JPCERT/CC - https://www.jpcert.or.jp/
  * NISC - https://www.nisc.go.jp/

A complete list of approved source agencies (US DoD 8140, NIST NICE, ANSI,
ENISA, NCSC-UK, CREST, IPA, JPCERT, NISC, ...) is maintained in
`data/sources/agencies.json` and is itself an interface that contributors may
extend through the `add-source-agency` issue template.

